OL,4,Ctradition with blanket design
OL,5,Ccompetition
OL,7,FThe tradition dates back to the Second
OL,8,FWorld War, when soldiers deployed in
OL,9,Fharsh conditions sought to bring some
OL,10,FChristmas cheer to bleak positions.
OL,12,FA regiment-wide blanket decorating
OL,13,Fcompetition evolved during the war,
OL,14,Fwith the owner of the best-looking
OL,15,Fblanket crowned the winner.
OL,17,FThe troops will remain in Cyprus over
OL,18,Fthe festive season as part of the
OL,19,FBritish Army's high-readiness standby
OL,20,Fforce.
